          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">N</hi>OW hardly here and there a hackney coach</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-2" n="2">Appearing, show'd the ruddy morn's approach.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-3" n="3">Now <hi rend="italics">Betty</hi> from her master's bed had flown,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-4" n="4">And softly stole to discompose her own.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-5" n="5">The slipshod 'prentice from his master's door,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-6" n="6">Had par'd the street, and springled round the floor.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-7" n="7">Now <hi rend="italics">Moll</hi> had whirl'd her mop with dext'rous airs,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-8" n="8">Prepar'd to scrub the entry and the stairs.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-9" n="9">The youth with broomy stumps began to trace</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-10" n="10">The kennel edge, where wheels had worn the place.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-11" n="11">The smallcoal-man was heard with cadence deep,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-12" n="12">'Til drown'd in shriller notes of chimney-sweep.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-13" n="13">Duns at his lordship's gate began to meet:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-14" n="14">And brickdust <hi rend="italics">Moll</hi> had scream'd thro' half a street.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-15" n="15">The turn-key now his flock returning sees,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-16" n="16">Duly let out a' nights to steal for fees.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-17" n="17">The watchful bailiffs take their silent stands;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-46L5-line-18" n="18">And school-boys lag with satchels in their hands.</l>
          </lg>
